After allies, including Germany, agreed to supply Kyiv with battle tanks, discussions began regarding the transfer of fighter jets, which Ukraine insists on.
Here Scholz took a categorical position: Germany would under no circumstances transfer combat aircraft.
At the same time, the Chancellor continues to assure that his country will support Kyiv &quot;for as long as necessary.&quot;
He made relevant statements after his meeting with Zelensky and French President Emmanuel Macron on February 8, and before the summit of European Union leaders on Thursday.
